    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="262"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/806: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 19, July 15, 1 p.m.,<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d262fn6">Not printed.</note> the Legation has not received any
                    communication from the Ministry of <pb facs="0263" n="253" xml:id="pg_253"/>
                    Foreign Affairs announcing change in the Government or requesting
                    recognition.</p>
                <p>Associated Press release published this morning quotes the Secretary of State as
                    having stated that he believed that it is not necessary for the United States to
                    consider the question of recognition.</p>
                <p>All members of Junta now in La Paz took oath of office July 14, 3 p.m. La Paz and
                    apparently entire country normal.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
